May 1st, 2017

Three Projects in SRTT

Utilizing the r package dlayr, calculate delays from gtfs and gps positions.

  1. Scale the deployment realtime-bus-sms across new agencies
  2. Improving routing information for Google and other mapping services
  3. Building a device to capture gps and real-time metadata in the field, like bike rack availability.

1. Scaling SMS Messaging

The SMS app needs the stop ID, route ID, and delay.

  • Provide this through a web API with an endpoint for stop ID to return delay info using r package plumber.

  • Build the SMS app deployment into this project.

  • An easy project we could do now to port the SMS app off bustracker? …using existing delay info from XML?

2. Improving routing through Public Transit.

You're visiting Fairbanks, AK, it's -40C and you want travel across town but you have no car! The fastest route could take you over two different bus routes (A or B).

After asking Google maps, you determine that the fastest route is A but you see the B bus is pulling up right now. You know that you will need to walk a longer distance from where A drops you off to your destination then from where B drops you off to your destination.

Would you jump on the B route to get out from the cold?

2. Improving routing through Public Transit.

  • Calculating the delays for these routes and providing it into the Google protocol buffer format allows the mapping services to incorporate the delays into routing.

  • We only need the gtfs and gps feed to make this happen!
